 normal Text is laid out using default settings. &lt;string&gt; When rendering text, the list of OpenType feature tags is passed to the text layout engine to enable or disable font features.&nbsp; For example, &quot;tagx=1&quot; implies that the OpenType feature 'tagx' is enabled.&nbsp; Using a value of 0 disables a given feature.&nbsp; For non-boolean OpenType features (e.g. stylistic alternates), the value implies a particular glyph to be selected.

